{"questionId":"9084723","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Another explosion is produced at X. The sound from this explosion is detected twice at the geophone at Z. Some sound travels directly from X to Z through clay along <strong>path 2</strong>. Other sound travels through clay via Y along <strong>path 3</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/9ae9cf3d56525411f1848a7ce8ed2e2b76c80f40.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The vertical thickness of the clay layer is <em>d</em>. The distance XZ is 80.0 m.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The time between the arrival of the sounds due to the path difference is 6.67 ms.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate <em>d</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>distance difference&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3000</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00667</mn><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math> m&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>½ distance difference&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></math> m so YZ&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></math> m&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><msqrt><msup><mtext>YZ</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mtext>XZ</mtext><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>49</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>40</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br>29.8 m&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>Recognises situation as (almost) 3:4:5 triangle&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br>30 m (<em>1 sf answer only accepted in this route</em>)&nbsp;✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9084723","referenceCode":"EXE.2.HL.TZ0.2d","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Calculate d.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A. Space, time and motion","A.1 Kinematics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}